    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Capris Haven't Changed</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Allison Brown letter on Jennifer Moses's May 31 article holds capri pants have never been flattering</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Aisles of Capris,'' by Jennifer Moses (Op-Ed, May 31):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Aisles of Capris,'' by Jennifer Moses (Op-Ed, May 31):</p>
        <p>I hope someone at the stores you mentioned reads your article. We used to call them pedal pushers. They were unflattering then and they're unflattering now!</p>
        <p>ALLISON BROWN  Cape Elizabeth, Me., May 31, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
